3.00	Long-gun	Long gun	The term long gun is used to describe classes of firearm and cannon with longer barrels than other classes. In small arms, a long gun is designed to be fired braced against the shoulder, in contrast to a handgun, while in artillery a long gun would be contrasted with a howitzer or carronade.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/Afulahagana.jpg/250px-Afulahagana.jpg
